        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4325396719" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10199626295252865268">Well, friends, save your time and money. This is a boring book. It a random travelogue about several places that the author visited. He has written a lot of stuff, mostly about his travels and who he meets. Weiner claims he is looking for the area/place that has the most bliss but he really just travels to places that have an institute or study lab or some loose coordination about bliss. He is really talking about happiness and that has been measured for decades, maybe centuries. This would not </span>
  <span id="freeText10199626295252865268" style="display:none">Well, friends, save your time and money. This is a boring book. It a random travelogue about several places that the author visited. He has written a lot of stuff, mostly about his travels and who he meets. Weiner claims he is looking for the area/place that has the most bliss but he really just travels to places that have an institute or study lab or some loose coordination about bliss. He is really talking about happiness and that has been measured for decades, maybe centuries. This would not hold us for a senior thesis/term paper.<br />He likes to describe the people he meets and his activities (eating, being in a lab or office, or walking) with them. At the end, he says that he is not quite happy yet. Big deal. I wonder how this got published. My book club is going to "discuss" it and that is how it fell into my hands. <br />Skip it. </span>
